            . I am servant to Mr. Benjamin Lambert, of <placeName id="t18310908-398-crimeloc2050">Old-street-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-398-crimeloc2050" type="placeName" value="Old-street-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-398-crimeloc2050" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-398-off2048 t18310908-398-crimeloc2050"></join>. On a Wednesday in September the prisoner came to his shop, and asked the price of some blacking - I said 4d. a bottle; I saw him take a pair of boots off a nail at the end of the counter, and put them into his hat - he then asked me if we had any cheaper blacking: I said No; he walked out - I ran to the door, and called my master, who was down stairs - the prisoner was taken to Worship-street.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-398-person2847">
                  JOHN 
                  MORLEY
               <interp inst="t18310908-398-person2847" type="surname" value="MORLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-398-person2847" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-398-person2847" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Police-officer. I took the prisoner, and found the boots in his hat, on Wednesday the 7th of September.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. A boy took the boots off a nail, I ran and took them from him, and they took me; I said,"Here are the boots, but I did not steal them."</p>
               <p>One witness gave the prisoner a good character.</p>
